The article is a statement by the President on the confirmation of Mel Watt as the head of an agency responsible for enforcing rules in the mortgage industry. The President highlights the progress made in the housing market since the housing bubble burst, with rising home values, increased construction, and fewer foreclosures. The President also mentions his strategy to help middle-class families buy homes and provide relief to responsible homeowners. Mel Watt, who has represented North Carolina in Congress for 20 years, is described as the right person to protect hardworking Americans and ensure that another housing crisis does not occur. The President thanks the Senate for confirming Watt's nomination and looks forward to his work on behalf of the American people.